🦇 Blind Bat Navigator (BBN) v1.0

Echolocation-based reasoning using friction as signal

⸻

🧭 Core Definition

BBN = a navigation system that emits structured intent and reads returning friction to map the invisible topology of a domain.

You don’t “see” the system.

You:
	•	emit (ideas, prompts, structures)
	•	listen (friction, constraints, corrections)
	•	infer shape

⸻

🧠 Core Mechanism (Echolocation Loop)

Emit → Receive → Interpret → Update → Re-emit

	•	Emit → a structured idea or probe
	•	Receive → response + friction
	•	Interpret → what constraint reflected back
	•	Update → refine your internal map
	•	Re-emit → adjusted probe

⸻

🧱 Signal Types (What the “echo” is made of)

Every response has two layers:

1. Content Signal
	•	The actual answer
	•	What the system can do

⸻

2. Friction Signal (the important one)
	•	Corrections
	•	Tone shifts
	•	Boundaries
	•	Missing clarity

👉 This tells you:

Where the walls are

⸻

🌊 Depth Mapping via Echo

